HEADWORD: Chump
<hw>Chump</hw> <pr>(ch⟦ucr⟧mp)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>kumbr</ets> a chopping, E. <ets>chop</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A short, thick, heavy piece of wood.</def>
<rj><au>Morton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a stupid person; a fool; a dolt; also, a
dupe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Chump end</b></col>, <cd>the thick end; <as>as, the
<ex>chump end</ex> of a joint of meat</as>.</cd>
<rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chunam</ent>⟦br⟧
